// Cross-statute discrimination — the eval file that exists BECAUSE section
// numbers collide and similar powers live in different acts. Each case expects
// exactly its own statute's provision and forbids the lookalikes. This is the
// regression guard for statute-qualified retrieval + the contextualized
// embeddings: if these fail, retrieval is routing questions to the wrong act.
//
// The "arrest" quadruple: four bodies, four arrest powers, four phrasings.
{"id": "x-arrest-01", "question": "police caught me spraying a wall, can they handcuff me right there for such a small offence", "lang": "en", "expect": [{"statute": "MOA1955", "section": "31"}], "forbid": [{"statute": "DDA1952", "section": "31"}], "should_find": true}
{"id": "x-arrest-02", "question": "can a majlis officer detain me over an unpaid licence issue or does he have to call the police", "lang": "en", "expect": [{"statute": "LGA1976", "section": "121"}], "forbid": [{"statute": "DDA1952", "section": "31"}], "should_find": true}
{"id": "x-arrest-03", "question": "the town council guy wants to arrest me for my stall blocking the walkway, is that even allowed", "lang": "en", "expect": [{"statute": "SDBA1974", "section": "46"}], "should_find": true}
{"id": "x-arrest-04", "question": "if the police suspect me of holding drugs can they grab me without any warrant", "lang": "en", "expect": [{"statute": "DDA1952", "section": "31"}], "forbid": [{"statute": "MOA1955", "section": "31"}], "should_find": true}
//
// Possession vs presumption routing: the offence and the burden-shifter are
// different sections — the presumption slice must surface for "it wasn't mine".
{"id": "x-drugs-01", "question": "what exactly is the offence of having drugs on you in malaysia", "lang": "en", "expect": [{"statute": "DDA1952", "section": "12"}], "should_find": true}
{"id": "x-drugs-02", "question": "they found pills in my glovebox but I swear I didnt know, does the law assume its mine", "lang": "en", "expect": [{"statute": "DDA1952", "section": "37"}], "should_find": true}
